gland","Bradpole, Dorset, England":"Bradpole, Dorset, England","Bradpole,Dorset,England.":"Bradpole, Dorset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Normandie Province, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1190–about 1230":"1190–about 1230","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1204–Male":"1204–Deceased","1209–1256":"1209–1256","1212–1263":"1212–1263","1215–1271":"1215–1271","1190–1230":"1190–1230","1190":"1190","1230":"1230","1263":"1263","1271":"1271","1180":"1180","1228":"1228","abt 1204":"about 1204","1215":"1215","1204":"1204","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1256":"1256","1209":"1209","about 1230":"about 1230","Long Ashton, Somerset, England":"Long Ashton, Somerset, England","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Bridport, , Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","Bradpole, Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bradpole, Dorset, England","Bradpole, Dorset, England":"Bradpole, Dorset, England","Bradpole,Dorset,England.":"Bradpole, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","Normandie Province, France":"Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Witt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["North German: nickname for someone with white hair or a remarkably pale complexion, from Middle Low German <i>witte</i> ‘white’.","South German: from a short form of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Wittigo</i>. This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine).","English (Hampshire and Wiltshire): variant of   White  ."],"variants":[{"name":"White","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>white</i>, <i>wit</i> (Old English <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’), hence a nickname for someone with white hair or a pale complexion. In some cases it is perhaps from a Middle English survival of the Old English personal name <i>Hwīta</i>, a short form of names in <i>Hwīt-</i> (from <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’). The name may also be topographic, referring to someone who lived by a bend or curve in a river or road (from Old English <i>wiht</i> ‘bend’), the source of the placename of Great Whyte in Ramsey, Huntingdonshire (compare   Wight  ). This name is also a variant of   Wight  . The surname <i>White</i> is also very common among African Americans.","Irish and Scottish: adopted for any of several Irish and Scottish Gaelic names based on <i>bán</i> ‘white, fair’ (see   Bain   1,   McElwain  ) or <i>fionn</i> ‘fair’ (see   Finn   1). The English surname has been Gaelicized in Ireland as <b>de Faoite</b>.","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames meaning ‘white’, for example German   Weiss  , French   Blanc  , Polish <b>Białas</b> (see   Bialas  ), Slovenian   Belec  , or any other synonymous Slavic surname beginning with <i>Bel-</i>, <i>Bev-</i>, <i>Biel-</i> or <i>Bil-</i>."]},{"name":"Witte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Franz, Kurt, Erwin, Gerhard, Dieter, Egon, Fritz, Gerhart, Lorenz, Eldor, Erhart.","German: variant of   Witt  .","Dutch: nickname for someone with white or blonde hair or an unusually pale complexion, from Middle Dutch <i>witte</i> ‘white’. Compare   De Witte  ."]},{"name":"Witts","meanings":["English: variant of   Witt  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Americanized form of German   Witz   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":34,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Actina de Witt of Bradpole was born in 1190, in Bradpole, Dorset, England. She married William de Morville I in 1209, in Bridport, Dorset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. She died about 1230, in Bridport, Dorset, England, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1190–about 1230":"1190–umbes 1230","1180–1228":"1180–1228","1204–Male":"1204–Surnud","1209–1256":"1209–1256","1212–1263":"1212–1263","1215–1271":"1215–1271","1190–1230":"1190–1230","1190":"1190","1230":"1230","1263":"1263","1271":"1271","1180":"1180","1228":"1228","abt 1204":"umbes 1204","1215":"1215","1204":"1204","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1256":"1256","1209":"1209","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Long Ashton, Somerset, England":"Long Ashton, Somerset, England","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Bridport, , Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bradpole, Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bradpole, Dorset, England","Bradpole, Dorset, England":"Bradpole, Dorset, England","Bradpole,Dorset,England.":"Bradpole, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Normandie Province, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi"